calculateEventLogLikelihood

private double calculateEventLogLikelihood(boolean involvesDuplication,
                                           boolean involvesHostShift,
                                           int nLosses,
                                           double branchTime)
Calculates the log likelihood of a series of cophylogenetic events occurring over a period of time.

Probability of n events with rate \lambda over t time calculated as follows:

P(n | \lambda, t) = (\lambda * t) ^ n * e ^ (-\lambda * t) / n!

This implementation should be more efficient, but cannot handle more than one each of duplication and host-shift events.

Parameters:
involvesDuplication - involves duplication event
involvesHostShift - involves host-shift event
nLosses - # of loss events
branchTime - branch length/time
Returns:
log likelihood of events in time
